Added GapShuffler; tweaks to RNG, StatefulRNG

GapShuffler allows getting a random ordering of elements from a
collection as an infinite Iterable, but won't ever repeat an element
(based on its index) close in order to a previous occurrence of that
element (there's a gap between occurrences of any one element). RNG now
allows any Collection in shuffle() but still returns an ArrayList, which
shouldn't break any code unless it subclassed RNG, and allows Sets and
Queues to be shuffled as well. StatefulRNG, when setRandomness() is
called with a RandomnessSource that isn't a LightRNG (which wasn't
recommended in the first place), now uses 64 random bits from that
source instead of 32, matching the existing behavior of the constructor.
This shouldn't affect much, but if your code wants consistent behavior
from a seed with StatefulRNG, setting the seed as a long is the best and
easiest way with StatefulRNG.

Indexing added to OrderedMap, testing usage

You can now get an item (meaning a key, value, or key-value pair as a
Map.Entry) from an OrderedMap given its index in the iteration order,
without actually doing any iteration and in constant time. You can also,
as a result, get random items. Reordering is currently limited to
shuffling the iteration order, but work is under way to allow more
complex reordering, possibly in a simple a way as giving a list of keys
to iterate through. This only applies to OrderedMap right now, not
IntDoubleOrderedMap yet. Several other classes have been refactored
slightly to test-drive OrderedMap internally, and it seems to behave
identically in LanguageTest (where IntDoubleMap is used) and doesn't
seem to have problems in other tests (the two ordered Maps should be
identical to LHMs but I can't tell the difference relative to
LinkedHashMap on some of them).

Add triage, which clusters together failures to be kinder to humans.

This loads failures from BigQuery, digests it into manageable clusters,
and uploads the resulting JSON to a GCS bucket for interactive browsing.

The frontend shows clusters with occurrence graphs and allows data to be
filtered.
Seed clusters with previous clustered output, to provide consistent cluster ids.

Format triage data as arrays of dicts, instead of arrays of arrays.

This is much easier to handle in statically typed languages, and avoids
having to remember arbitrary array indices to write code effectively.
Sort triage builds most recent first.

triage: fix previous cluster seeding.

Iterating through a dict yields its keys, so this line:

   for key, _id, _ftext, _clusters in previous_clustered:

Was assigning the variables the values:

   "id", "key", "tests", "text"

In random order.

Make a link to a specific triage cluster just render that cluster.

Remove illegal characters from XML strings before parsing.

It's easy for people to unintentionally inject XML-unsafe characters
into a string from a copy/paste when filling out the Description or
Testing Done fields of a review request.

We now sanitize the XML before attempting to parse it, removing any
illegal characters. The result is a string that can be safely parsed
with no noticeably defects.

Reviewed at https://reviews.reviewboard.org/r/6670/

Fix call to sanitize_illegal_chars_for_xml.

The newly-added sanitize_illegal_chars_for_xml method was being called after we
had encoded the unicode string into bytes, and doing the regular expression
substitution would then try to coerce those bytes back to unicode using the
ascii codec. Doing the sanitization on the unicode object, and then encoding to
bytes works correctly.

Loader now uses XDomainRequest in IE9 to load JSON data to help with CORS issues.

Loader.useXDomainRequest boolean added. If `true` (the default is `false`) it will use XDomainRequest when loading JSON files instead of xhr. In rare IE edge-cases this may be required. You'll know if you need it (#1131 #1116)
Loader.useXDomainRequest boolean automatically set to `true` if the browser is specifically detected as IE9, but you can still override this. IE10 will use xhr.

Phaser.AudioSprite

AudioSprite implementation for phaser.

Loads audio sprites based on the file format created with: https://github.com/tonistiigi/audiosprite

Loader.useXDomainRequest used to be enabled automatically for IE9 but is now always set to `false`. Please enable it only if you know your server set-up / CDN requires it, as some most certainly do, but we're finding them to be less and less used these days, so we feel it's safe to now disable this by default (#1248)

Loader.json was using the wrong context in IE9 with XDomainRequest calls (thanks @pnstickne #1258)
